<dl id="un3031h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un3" href="#un3031">UN3: </a>  <a href="../../FF/unbs/un3all.htm#un3031h"> (VIII.A.5) 31(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Sisyphus <small>Blue</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="un3031h"> <li>Ulysses unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Yea and I beheld <mark>Sisyphus</mark> in strong torment, grasping a monstrous stone with both his hands. He was pressing thereat with hands and feet, and trying to roll the stone upward toward the brow of the hill. But oft as he was about to hurl it over the top, the weight would drive him back, so once again to the plain rolled the stone, the shameless thing. <small> Homer, <a name="OHBL" href="/udra/udex.htm#OHBL"><cite title="source">The Odyssey</cite></a>, trans. Butcher &amp; Lang (1906), 190</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: In <i>Ulysses</i> episode &ldquo;Hades&rdquo;: Martin Cunningham. </mm> </dd></dl>
